name: 04-Model Training and Validation
content:
Model Training and Validation

Model Used:

  • Decision Tree Classifier (Spark ML) – selected for interpretability and ability to handle mixed data types.

Features Used:

  • severity_type, resource_type, event_type, volume, location, log_feature.

Feature Importance:

  • Decision Trees provide feature importance via information gain (entropy reduction).
  • Typically, resource_type and log_feature volume strongly influence severity prediction.

Model Metrics:

  • Accuracy – Overall prediction correctness.
  • Precision – Reliability of critical fault predictions.
  • Recall (Sensitivity) – Ability to correctly detect actual severe faults.
  • F1 Score – Balanced performance measure.

Validation Strategy:

  • Train/test split (e.g., 70/30).
  • Cross-validation for robustness.
  • Confusion matrix to analyze misclassified severity levels.

Predictive Analysis and Insights

  • Predict severity of new fault events (fault_severity = 0/1).
  • Highlight critical event types and locations for proactive action.
  • Support fault prioritization dashboards for network teams.
  • Drive strategic infrastructure upgrades by analyzing recurring high-severity patterns.
